{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ed676d13-570a-4996-a6a2-d5d2cc609f16","content":"Here's the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is passed directly to the test platform runner.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test projects):\n\n| Old behaviour | Package to add |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\n**In each test `.csproj`**, opt in to the new runner:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**Key mapping cheat-sheet:**\n\n| VSTest flag | Testing Platform flag |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `--report-trx` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` | `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `--crashdump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `--hangdump` |\n| `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` | `--hangdump-timeout 5m` |\n| `--filter` | `--filter` (unchanged, stays before `--`) |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5afc30b2-6ab2-41ab-8cd9-26ed32a2071f","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling changes, not a codebase task.\n\nLet me provide the equivalent command for Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nKey differences when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n1. `--filter` → `--filter` (same)\n2. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in)\n3. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` or use `--coverage --coverage-output-format cobertura` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage\n\n\n4. `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n5. `--blame-hang` → `--hangdump`\n6. `--blame-hang-timeout 5m` → `--hangdump-timeout 5m`\n\nFor .NET 8, you'll need to explicitly opt into Microsoft.Testing.Platform by setting the `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatform` property in your project file, since it's not the default until .NET 9.\n\nWith this setup, the command-line arguments shift significantly. Most filters and loggers still work through `dotnet test`, but specialized features like crash dumps, code coverage, and TRX reporting require additional NuGet packages and use different flag names like `--report-trx` and `--coverage`. The required NuGet packages are `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` for TRX reporting, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage` for coverage collection, `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` for crash dumps, and `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` for hang detection.","outputTokens":1248,"requestId":"A02A:2C9D9E:C052CE:E137BE:69FE8696"},"id":"bc9c37dc-3b2c-4159-9368-c2ceaefa5fbd","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:58:19.241Z","parentId":"59ee9ee8-c35d-4aba-be07-8d31a9bd039a"}
